habitat_description:
This species has a restricted distribution in the northern Channel Islands off the Pacific Coast in south-central California; East Anacapa, Middle Anacapa, West Anacapa, Santa Cruz, and San Miguel islands (Wake and Jockusch 2000; Stebbins 2003). 
Habitat of adults includes under cow pies in open grassland, coastal sage scrub, riparian, oak woodlands, pine forest communities, and chaparral. Also known to occupy open areas near the ocean where they are abundantly found in the sand and under driftwood (Lannoo 2005; Wake and Jockusch 2000)
